Tachyons aren’t “moving fast”; they’re instantaneous stress propagators across the unbounded E8 reservoir (Δτ=0, no “speed” in non-temporal substrate), damping folding everywhere via infinite geometric reach. The Rebound isn’t braking them — it’s a localized compression wave (intense energy density from collapsing prior universe) that pushes a region past critical threshold, trapping photons into knots (mass creation) and unfolding spacetime despite Tachyon inhibition. This resolves why universes form at all in an otherwise flat, low-entropy SPF.
